sentence: Today's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index volume reaching the 1st place in the top ten list for this year.
The last time the index closed above 2.66 billion shares was on Mar 15 2013.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 2.7 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.49 to 1 ratio.
There were 1509 advancers and 1014 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 35 stocks reached a 52 week high and 35 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -.43% for the day; a total of -12.39 points.
Oracle Corporation ( ORCL ) had the largest percent change down (-9.26%) while DIRECTV ( DTV ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.76%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .28% for the day; a total of 41.08 points.
Hewlett-Packard Company ( HPQ ) had the largest percent change down (-2.31%) while Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.9%.
